make -f _fcrts.mak TARGET=4CPC DEBUG=0  PRODUCT="USE_CROSSTABLE" SOURCERY_GCC=1 all

SOURCERY_GCC=1 to build with codesourcery gcc
FREESCALE_GCC=1 to build with freescale gcc
PRODUCT="USE_NO_CROSSTABLE" To build the runtime for TPAC hardware 
PRODUCT="USE_CROSSTABLE" To build the runtime for HW119 aka ATN01 or P04 hardware 

You can build the runtime only for one kind of hardware so the two define cannot be active at the same time
